Day 9 – Working with JSON & Building a Contact Book

Date: June 26, 2026

📚 Topics Learned
        JSON Data Management
        Concepts Covered
        Saving application data to JSON files.
        Loading data from JSON files.
        Converting objects into dictionaries using to_dict().
        Reconstructing objects from dictionaries using from_dict().
        Serializing and deserializing collections of objects.
        Organizing data persistence into separate helper functions.
        Handling file-related exceptions when reading and writing JSON.

💡 Key Takeaways
        JSON is an excellent format for storing structured application data.
        Separating data persistence logic from business logic makes programs easier to maintain.
        Custom Python objects must be converted into dictionaries before being stored as JSON.
        Well-designed classes simplify serialization and future expansion of a project.

🛠 Project Built
        Contact Book
        Features
        Add new contacts.
        View all saved contacts.
        Search contacts.
        Update existing contact information.
        Delete contacts.
        Save contacts to a JSON file.
        Load contacts automatically when the application starts.
        Skills Practiced
        Object-Oriented Programming
        Working with lists of objects
        JSON serialization and deserialization
        File handling
        Exception handling
        Modular programming
        CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations

🧠 Challenges Faced
        Converting a list of custom objects into JSON-serializable dictionaries.
        Loading JSON data back into Python objects.
        Debugging serialization errors such as unsupported object types.
        Designing methods that keep the code clean and reusable.

✅ What I Improved
        Improved understanding of data persistence.
        Became more comfortable organizing projects into multiple files.
        Learned how to separate application logic from storage logic.
        Improved debugging skills by resolving JSON serialization issues.
        Gained more experience designing larger Python projects.

📈 Progress Summary
        Today's Contact Book project strengthened my understanding of how real applications manage and persist data.
        I learned how to save collections of custom objects to JSON files and restore them when the application starts. 
        This project reinforced good software design practices by separating data storage from application logic and using 
        reusable methods for object conversion.

Project Completed:
        ✅ Contact Book

🚀 Skills Gained
        JSON file handling
        Object serialization
        Object deserialization
        CRUD application development
        Multi-file project organization
        Python debugging
        Data persistence